Description: Lip sherd of East Greek (North Ionian) pottery bowl-shaped cup; interior glazed orange; reserved on the outside except for line at top of lip; inscription cut on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.455)
